HEADWORD: Cytula
<hw>Cyt"u*la</hw> <pr>(s?t"?-l?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>ky`tos</grk> a hollow vessel.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>The fertilized egg cell or parent cell, from the development of
which the child or other organism is formed.</def>
